            <div class="campus">
                <h1>
                    RESEARCH SUPPORT
                </h1>
                <br>
                <p>
                    <span>Overview of Research Support Services:</span> Provide an introduction to the research support services available at the university, highlighting the various ways in which the university supports faculty and staff in their research activities.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Funding Opportunities: </span> Detail the internal and external funding opportunities available to faculty and staff for research projects, including grants, fellowships, awards, and seed funding. Provide information on eligibility criteria, application procedures, and deadlines.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Grant Proposal Development:</span> Offer guidance and resources to assist faculty and staff in developing competitive grant proposals, including workshops, templates, and proposal writing guides. Highlight successful grant proposals and funding statistics to showcase the university's track record in securing research funding.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Research Administration:</span> Provide information on research administration services, including assistance with proposal submission, budget development, compliance requirements, and project management. Offer contact information for research administrators who can provide personalized support and guidance.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Research Ethics and Compliance:</span> Explain the university's policies and procedures regarding research ethics, integrity, and compliance with regulatory requirements. Offer resources and training opportunities on topics such as human subjects research, animal welfare, biosafety, and intellectual property rights.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Collaborative Research Opportunities:</span> Highlight opportunities for interdisciplinary collaboration and partnerships within the university and with external institutions. Showcase existing research centers, institutes, and collaborative initiatives where faculty and staff can engage in collaborative research projects.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Research Facilities and Infrastructure:</span> Provide information on research facilities, laboratories, equipment, and technical services available to support faculty and staff in their research activities. Include details on access procedures, usage policies, and technical support services.
                    <br><br>
                    <span>Professional Development:</span> Offer professional development opportunities tailored to the needs of faculty and staff engaged in research, including workshops, seminars, and training programs on topics such as research methods, data analysis, scholarly publishing, and research dissemination.
                </p>
